src_Destination_Table: The destination table in src Schema
Source_File: The name of the source file without the dates. i.e. IWS_POSITD
Date_Format: The format of the date in the header row of the source file
Header_Delimiter: The delimiter of the header row of the file. If the column is blank, it is assumed the header is fixed width.
Date_Position_OR_Column: Depending on the file being delimited or fixed width, column number or character starting position of the date string.
Additional_Delimiter: Optional for files containing multiple delimiters. i.e. ',' and '|'.
File_Type: The type of file. Pipe Delimited, Comma Delimited, Fixed Width, JSON
XLS_to_CSV: Some files are .xls and need to be converted to .csv
XLS_Sheet_Name: If a file needs to be converted from XLS to CSV and a specific sheet needs to be extracted, list the sheet name here. If there is only one sheet, it can be left blank.
Number_Of_Quarters: Only if File_Type = SQL. Number of quarters to download data from SQL. If it's 0, it will select all records. The code assumes the column name for the quarter is "Quarter".
Unzip_File: Run the script to Unzip files
